    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 25, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 💀 The Iran Peace Talks Collapsed Before They Could Start\n\nDay 56 of the US-Iran conflict: Vance's second-round trip to Islamabad was called off, Iran's Foreign Ministry confirmed \"no meeting is planned,\" and the Strait of Hormuz remains effectively closed to commercial traffic.\n\n- **The maritime standoff:** The US military is boarding tankers; Iran has attacked three commercial ships and seized two. Both sides call the other the \"main obstacle\" to negotiations. This is what diplomacy looks like when neither party wants to negotiate.\n- **The Trump extension:** Trump extended the ceasefire indefinitely, offering time for Tehran to \"unify around a proposal.\" Tehran's unified position appears to be: no meeting.\n\n*A ceasefire with no peace talks and an active shoot-to-kill order is just war with better \"branding.\"*\n\n**Sources:** [CNN](https://www.cnn.com/2026/04/24/world/live-news/iran-war-trump-israel-lebanon) | [NBC News](https://www.nbcnews.com/world/iran/live-blog/live-updates-trump-iran-hormuz-blockade-ceasefire-talks-lebanon-israel-rcna341571) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/23/iran-war-whats-happening-on-day-55-after-trump-extended-ceasefire)\n\n---\n\n## 🔌 Congress Wants to Close the AI Chip Loophole. The White House Is Selling Chips.\n\nThe House Foreign Affairs Committee advanced a bipartisan slate of export control bills on April 23, targeting loopholes that allow Nvidia chips and advanced AI hardware to reach China.\n\n- **The contradiction:** In January 2026, the Trump administration quietly expanded these exact channels — shifting from a presumption of denial to case-by-case review for advanced chip exports to China. Congress now wants to reverse course.\n- **The timeline:** Soften export controls in January. Approve higher-tier chip sales in March. Hold hearings about dangerous loopholes in April. No notes.\n\n*US tech policy on China: sanction the chips on Monday, approve the exports on Tuesday, hold hearings about the loopholes on Wednesday.*\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-23/ai-export-control-measures-aimed-at-china-gain-steam-in-us-house) | [CFR](https://www.cfr.org/articles/new-ai-chip-export-policy-china-strategically-incoherent-and-unenforceable)\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Trump Threatens 100% Tariffs on Russia's Trade Partners (Russia Is Exempt)\n\nTrump threatened 100% secondary tariffs on any country trading with Russia if no Ukraine peace deal materializes within 50 days — while simultaneously exempting Russia from the main US tariff regime to avoid disrupting peace talks.\n\n- **The geometry:** Ukraine, the invaded country, faces a 10% export duty to the US. Russia, the invading country, is exempt from the broader tariff regime. The logic is its own kind of thing.\n- **The 50-day clock:** If no deal in 50 days, countries trading with Russia — which describes most of Asia, Europe, and the Global South — face 100% tariffs.\n\n*Exempt Russia from tariffs. Threaten to tariff everyone else unless Russia stops the war it's exempt from tariffs for. Diplomacy.*\n\n**Sources:** [PBS News](https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/trump-threatens-to-impose-tariffs-on-russia-if-they-dont-end-ukraine-war-within-50-days) | [Kyiv Post](https://www.kyivpost.com/post/50321) | [Russia Matters](https://www.russiamatters.org/analysis/secondary-tariffs-or-tighter-sanctions-strategies-end-russias-war-ukraine)"
  }
